# Contributing

Thanks for your interest in contributing to AI Gallery Mini Program 🎨

We welcome contributions of all kinds, including:

- 🐛 Bug fixes
- ✨ New features
- 📖 Documentation improvements
- ⚡ Performance optimizations
- 🎨 UI/UX enhancements
- 🧪 Tests and code quality improvements

Please read the guidelines below before submitting changes.

---

## Development Workflow

### 1. Fork the repository

Create your own fork and clone it locally:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ai-gallery-miniprogram.git
cd ai-gallery-miniprogram
```

### 2. Create a feature branch

Please avoid committing directly to the main branch.

Use meaningful branch names:

```bash
# Feature
git checkout -b feature/image-style-selector

# Bug fix
git checkout -b fix/login-state-error

# Refactor
git checkout -b refactor/gallery-service
```

Branch naming suggestions:

| Type | Example |
|--------|---------|
| feature | feature/user-gallery |
| fix | fix/image-cache |
| refactor | refactor/auth-service |
| docs | docs/update-readme |
| chore | chore/dependencies |

---

## Local Development Setup

### Requirements

- Node.js >= 14
- WeChat Developer Tools (latest recommended)
- Tencent Cloud CloudBase account
- Mini Program developer permissions

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Configure project environment:

```bash
# project.config.json

{
  "cloudfunctionRoot":"cloudfunctions/",
  "cloudbase":{
    "env":"your-env-id"
  }
}
```

Upload cloud functions if needed:

```bash
tcb functions:deploy -e your-env-id
```

Open the project using WeChat Developer Tools.

---

## Project Structure

```text
ai-gallery-miniprogram/
├── cloudfunctions/
├── miniprogram/
│   ├── pages/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── config/
│   ├── types/
│   └── styles/
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

General guidelines:

- `pages/` → page-level logic
- `components/` → reusable components
- `utils/` → shared utilities
- `types/` → TypeScript definitions
- `cloudfunctions/` → backend business logic

Keep responsibilities clear and avoid large mixed files.

---

## Coding Guidelines

### TypeScript

Prefer strong typing:

```typescript
interface UserInfo {
  openid: string
  nickname: string
  avatar: string
}
```

Avoid:

```typescript
const user: any = {}
```

Use:

```typescript
const user: UserInfo = {}
```

---

### Naming Convention

#### Variables

```typescript
const imageUrl = ''
const galleryList = []
```

#### Components

```text
gallery-item/
prompt-input/
empty-state/
```

#### Cloud Functions

```text
generate-image
publish-work
user-login
```

Use descriptive names.

Avoid abbreviations unless widely understood.

---

### Component Principles

Components should:

- Have a single responsibility
- Avoid deeply nested logic
- Be reusable
- Keep business logic outside UI components when possible

Good:

```typescript
<gallery-item />
<prompt-input />
```

Avoid creating very large components handling unrelated behaviors.

---

## UI Guidelines

This project uses:

- WeChat Mini Program Native Framework
- TDesign Weixin

Please keep UI consistent:

- Follow existing spacing patterns
- Follow existing typography styles
- Reuse TDesign components whenever possible
- Avoid introducing duplicate component styles

Example:

```json
{
  "usingComponents": {
    "t-button": "tdesign-miniprogram/button/button",
    "t-input": "tdesign-miniprogram/input/input"
  }
}
```

---

## Cloud Function Guidelines

Cloud functions should:

- Validate all inputs
- Return consistent response structures
- Handle errors gracefully
- Avoid duplicated logic

Recommended response format:

```typescript
return {
  success: true,
  data,
  message: ''
}
```

Error example:

```typescript
return {
  success: false,
  message: 'Image generation failed'
}
```

---

## Commit Message Convention

Please follow conventional commit style:

```bash
feat: add AI style selector
fix: resolve login token issue
docs: update deployment guide
refactor: optimize gallery loading logic
chore: update dependencies
```

Common types:

| Type | Description |
|--------|---------|
| feat | New feature |
| fix | Bug fix |
| docs | Documentation |
| refactor | Code refactor |
| style | Formatting only |
| test | Tests |
| chore | Maintenance |

---

## Pull Request Guidelines

Before opening a PR:

Checklist:

- [ ] Code builds successfully
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] Cloud functions tested
- [ ] UI tested in WeChat Developer Tools
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed
- [ ] No unnecessary files included

PR descriptions should include:

```md
## Summary

Brief description of changes

## Changes

- Added ...
- Fixed ...
- Updated ...

## Screenshots

Add screenshots if UI changed

## Testing

Explain how changes were tested
```

---

## Reporting Issues

When creating an issue, include:

### Bug report

```md
Environment:
- WeChat version:
- Device:
- Node.js version:

Steps to reproduce:

1.
2.
3.

Expected behavior:

Actual behavior:

Screenshots:
```

### Feature request

```md
Problem:

Suggested solution:

Additional context:
```

